# afterwriting is a CLI wrapper around the same JS code that powers
# afterwriting.com — a web-based screenplay-formatting tool that converts
# Fountain (https://fountain.io) markup into formatted PDF screenplays
# with industry-standard layout (Courier 12pt, 1.5" left margin, dialogue
# centering, scene-heading rules).  Same renderer powers the desktop
# offline mode and the npm CLI.  Configuration is via JSON config file
# matching the schema documented in docs/clients.md (embolden_scene_-
# headers / show_page_numbers / split_dialogue / print_title_page /
# print_profile a4|usletter / scenes_numbers none|left|right|both /
# each_scene_on_new_page / font_family Courier|CourierPrime|Courier-
# PrimeCyrillic|Kosugi).  Snippets in the config allow templated
# character names that get expanded throughout the script.
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 174 CLOSES — pure-language PDF generation libraries =============
# === TRIPLE-229 ROUND-NUMBER LANDMARK · 167th AXIS CLOSED =================
# ============================================================================
# Axis position: TS-Node=229 CLOSES Axis 174 at slot 1/1/1 — quadruple-clean
